About

I love building anything and everything. I have a degree= in Mechatronic Engineering, have been coding for several years and I thriv= e off all forms of problem-solving. As well as being a technophile, I=E2=80= =99m extremely passionate about Entrepreneurship and am heavily involved wi= th start-ups. I love pushing boundaries with teams of remarkable, intellige= nt individuals who are motivated towards a common goal. I live for the long= nights, the adventures, the highs and the lows. I=E2=80=99m addicted to th= e chaos and the stresses!

I=E2=80=99ve never bonded with the no= tion of a profession defining one=E2=80=99s identity, nor did I buy into th= e facade of success being defined by the number of decades you spend climbi= ng the corporate ladder, slaving for a single company whilst dreaming of yo= ur retirement. I seek to inspire others to chase their dreams and take the = risks necessary to be able to spend their life doing meaningful work that t= hey love and can be proud of. The only way to do great work is to love what= you do.

This website is simply my little cor= ner of the internet. I hope that it may be able to inspire and teach whilst= concurrently helping to keep me accountable and motivated towards my own g= oals. 

Stay Hungry, Stay Foolish.

<= div class=3D"sqs-block-content">

=E2=80=9CWhen you grow up you tend to get told the world= is the way it is and your life is just to live your life inside the world.= Try not to bash into the walls too much. Try to have a nice family, have f= un, save a little money.

That=E2=80=99s a very limited life. Life can be much broader once y= ou discover one simple fact, and that is - everything around you that you= call life, was made up by people that were no smarter than you. And you ca= n change it, you can influence it, you can build your own things that other= people can use=E2=80=A6

Shake off this erroneous notion that life is there and you=E2=80= =99re just gonna life in it, versus embrace it, change it, improve it, make= your mark upon it=E2=80=A6 Once you learn that, you=E2=80=99ll never be th= e same again.=E2=80=9D

=E2=80=94 Steve Jobs

My Reading List

Books are the single most overlooked source of = easily obtainable knowledge. Wrapped up in their pages are the thoughts of = countless men and women who are significantly smarter than I. It=E2=80=99s = truely incredible! Many spend astronomical amounts on higher education with= out giving thought to all the wisdom collecting dust in their local library= .

In 20= 20, I have a goal to read at least 52 books (yes, one per week for those wh= o are on the ball). In order to keep myself accountable and on track I have= decided to write brief recaps of each of the books I read. Who knows, hope= fully some of my thoughts might even spark your interest and you=E2=80=99ll= find your next book to read too.
